olive oil
1 packet basmati rice
1 cucumber
1 packet beef mince
1 packet fine breadcrumbs
1 sachet chermoula spice blend
1 egg
1 sachet Bengal Curry Paste
1 tsp honey
½ packet cream
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a medium saucepan with the boiling water.
• Add basmati rice and a pinch of salt and cook, uncovered, over high heat until tender, 12 minutes. Drain.

• Meanwhile, slice cucumber into half-moons.
• In a large bowl, combine beef mince, fine breadcrumbs, chermoula spice blend and egg.
• Using damp hands, roll beef mixture into koftas about 8cm long and 2.5cm thick (3 per person).

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat.
• Cook koftas, turning regularly, until browned and cooked through, 10-12 minutes (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded).
• Remove from heat, and add the honey, turning to coat.

• In a large bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, cucumber, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and a drizzle of olive oil. Season to taste.
• Divide rapid rice, beef koftas and cucumber salad between bowls. Pour Moroccan sauce over koftas. Enjoy!